Hmm, I wonder if this was a specific block for all connections on port 22 or if there was some other mechanisms involved. Very curious.

The situation in Belarus is what I thought may be possible to happen in the United States the way things were heading here. I drew a blueprint for a decentralized internet that would use cellphones, routers, laptops, and other WiFi enabled devices last Summer and found a nice project in Germany known as Freifunk (German for Free Radio) that is similar and gaining much popularity. It also supports connection to the wider internet like my concept does, but they do not involve anything except routers. So, perhaps it would be something to look into for you as well. 

There are many small groups that run the Freifunk Networks in various cities (primarily in Germany at this time,) but they have offered to help me establish similar networks here in the USA. They should be more than willing to help you all as well I am sure. The main website for them is here:

https://freifunk.net/en/
